  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\nThis compiles:\r\n```python\r\n@public\r\n@constant\r\n@payable\r\ndef get_real() -> decimal:\r\n    return 0.0\r\n```\r\nI don't think `@payable` and `@constant` should be allowed to be together because changing the balance of ether of the smart contract is modifying the underlying state.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\nAdd an exception if they're both present\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n![baby rhino](https://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/2029718f4118781dc0c3283af0e2d030be823a9d/c=140-0-3371-2429&r=x404&c=534x401/local/-/media/2016/10/17/IAGroup/DesMoines/636123108878450705-RRW85964.JPG)\r\n",
